is victory over Roger Federer in 2012 to claim gold at Wimbledon was the biggest achievement of his life to that point, and gave him the belief to return to SW19 a year later and win his maiden title there.\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1005, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roger Federer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His victory\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"Wimbledon\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest achievement\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"the belief\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1132}, {\"ngram\": \"SW19\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"his maiden title\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And when he beat Juan Martin del Potro to retain the Olympic title four years later in Rio de Janeiro, he became the first singles player ever to win two singles gold medals.\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9962242992050709, \"rank\": 0.003789956384912443, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}, {\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999999991648565, \"rank\": 8.352218111853898e-10, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic title\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"the first singles player\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"two singles gold medals\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is perhaps fitting then that Murray will close the curtain on his career at the Olympic Games, albeit an incongruous setting given clay is his least favourite surface and Roland Garros his least successful major.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2618612414217377e-38, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999986861921106, \"rank\": 9.50048428971673e-07, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the curtain\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"an incongruous setting\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1500}, {\"ngram\": \"clay\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"his least favourite surface\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"his least successful major\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1587}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the former world No 1 and three-time grand slam winner has had to learn that he could not entirely control the timing or venue of his departure from the professional game: tearing ankle ligaments in March and then having back surgery just days before his last Wimbledon put paid to that.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No 1 and three-time grand slam winner\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"the timing\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1711}, {\"ngram\": \"venue\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"his departure\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1737}, {\"ngram\": \"the professional game\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"tearing ankle ligaments\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"back surgery\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"his last Wimbledon\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wasn't sure how I would feel a few months ago, to be honest,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1956, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was unsure about it.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had a lot of conversations with my family, with my wife.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 1993}, {\"ngram\": \"conversations\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2010}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"my wife\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was unsure about the injury during Queen's, but I had been struggling with my back through most of the clay-court season after the ankle injury.\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2187, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the injury\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"Queen\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2083}, {\"ngram\": \"my back\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2125}, {\"ngram\": \"the clay-court season\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"the ankle injury\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that it was the right time and I am happy about it now.\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2252, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the right time\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not feel that way a few months ago when I [first] thought this is when I was going to stop.\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that way\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not really want to, whereas now I want to and I know that it's the right time for me, so I feel good about it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the right time\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2436}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It means that Murray's last singles match will be his retirement against Jordan Thompson, a match where the Scot felt a cyst in his back flare up as he walked to the court, leaving him without feeling or coordination in his right leg.\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2618612414217377e-38, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2545, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Thompson_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.9920171090555051, \"rank\": 0.0037318405970944053, \"text\": \"Jordan Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Thompson_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Thompson_(tennis)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his retirement\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2536}, {\"ngram\": \"a match\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"the Scot\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2584}, {\"ngram\": \"a cyst\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"his back flare\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 261